    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A thematic, single-page scrolling application designed to guide the user through the narrative of the US-India tariff dispute. The structure begins with a high-level summary (The Core Issue), delves into the quantitative evidence (The Energy Shift), exposes the central conflict (The 'Double Standard' Debate), and concludes with the broader consequences (Ripple Effects). This thematic flow is more intuitive for user exploration than a rigid report structure, allowing users to grasp the 'what', 'why', and 'so what' of the situation through interactive charts and focused content blocks. Navigation is facilitated by a sticky header, enabling easy access to each thematic section. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        1. India's Oil Imports: Report Info -> Drastic shift in India's oil suppliers post-Ukraine invasion. Goal -> Show change over time. Viz -> Interactive Doughnut Chart (Chart.js). Interaction -> A button toggles between 'Pre-2022' and 'Post-2022' data, dynamically updating the chart to visually represent the dramatic rise of Russian oil. Justification -> This interaction makes the data-driven narrative compelling and easy to understand.
        2. India vs. China Comparison: Report Info -> China imports more Russian oil but faces lower US tariffs than India. Goal -> Compare entities across different metrics. Viz -> Grouped Bar Chart (Chart.js). Interaction -> Hover tooltips display precise values for oil imports ($B) and tariff rates (%). Justification -> A grouped bar chart is the most effective way to directly compare the two countries on these two different scales, making the 'double standard' argument visually evident.
        3. Key Stats: Report Info -> 50% total tariff, 21-day deadline. Goal -> Inform with high-impact numbers. Viz -> Large-font text blocks (HTML/Tailwind). Justification -> Emphasizes the severity and urgency of the situation immediately.
        4. Core Arguments & Implications: Report Info -> US justification, India's response, geopolitical consequences. Goal -> Organize and explain qualitative insights. Viz -> Styled cards and text sections using HTML/Tailwind. Justification -> Breaks down complex information into digestible, thematically organized chunks for better readability.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
